WEBVTT

1
00:00:37.705 --> 00:00:38.706
Ah!

2
00:02:01.789 --> 00:02:05.417
The first and last
thing my mama gave me...

3
00:02:07.837 --> 00:02:10.798
...was apologies.

4
00:03:02.808 --> 00:03:05.060
What?

5
00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:08.480
Expect me to howl?

6
00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:12.151
I hadn't had that much
moonshine. no.

7
00:03:12.151 --> 00:03:14.737
I want to talk to you.

8
00:03:14.737 --> 00:03:19.325
Well. we talking.
Now what?

9
00:03:22.411 --> 00:03:25.623
What can I do for you.
Caesar?

10
00:03:35.215 --> 00:03:38.594
I'm heading back north.

11
00:03:38.594 --> 00:03:41.513
Soon.

12
00:03:41.513 --> 00:03:44.683
Running away. and
I want you to come with.

13
00:03:44.683 --> 00:03:48.312
You heading north?

14
00:03:48.312 --> 00:03:51.065
And I'm gonna eat.

15
00:03:51.065 --> 00:03:54.151
No. please. Cora.

16
00:03:54.151 --> 00:03:57.321
I don't want you to tell on me.
Have to trust you on that.

17
00:03:57.321 --> 00:04:00.449
But I'm getting on away
from here; I have to.

18
00:04:00.449 --> 00:04:03.619
Well. what you want me for?

19
00:04:06.747 --> 00:04:09.708
Good luck.

20
00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:11.835
Good luck?

21
00:04:13.754 --> 00:04:17.633
Now you listen here. Caesar.

22
00:04:17.633 --> 00:04:19.969
I know you ain't been
on this plantation long at all.

23
00:04:19.969 --> 00:04:22.680
but one thing you gots to know
by now is I ain't nobody's

24
00:04:22.680 --> 00:04:24.974
"good luck."

25
00:04:24.974 --> 00:04:28.143
Ain't nobody's...

26
00:05:35.335 --> 00:05:37.921
♪ In that old field ♪

27
00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:42.134
♪ In that old field ♪

28
00:05:44.386 --> 00:05:47.890
♪ In that old field...

29
00:05:47.890 --> 00:05:51.101
Now. Jockey. you got to eat
something. you hear?

30
00:05:51.101 --> 00:05:53.604
Mabel?

31
00:05:53.604 --> 00:05:55.939
No. Jockey. it's Cora.

32
00:05:55.939 --> 00:05:58.942
Mabel. where you been at?

33
00:06:00.736 --> 00:06:03.572
Easy. That's good.

34
00:06:03.572 --> 00:06:06.366
- Can you handle it?
- Mm-hmm.

35
00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:08.410
- Okay.
- That's good. Mmm.

36
00:06:10.204 --> 00:06:11.622
Mmm.

37
00:06:14.792 --> 00:06:17.461
♪ In that old field ♪♪

38
00:06:39.858 --> 00:06:43.946
Master James.
Master Terrance.

39
00:06:43.946 --> 00:06:46.865
Oh. don't let us bother you.

40
00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:49.284
My brother and I were
discussing business

41
00:06:49.284 --> 00:06:52.037
and heard the music.

42
00:06:53.789 --> 00:06:58.669
I told him. "Now that is
the most god-awful racket

43
00:06:58.669 --> 00:07:00.546
I ever heard."

44
00:07:00.546 --> 00:07:03.006
God. what a ruckus.

45
00:07:03.006 --> 00:07:05.884
We's sorry to disturb
you. Master Terrance.

46
00:07:05.884 --> 00:07:08.428
Oh. no. no. no. No. no.
No disturbance at all. Jockey.

47
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:10.222
No disturbance at all.

48
00:07:11.890 --> 00:07:17.104
You sure have a peculiar way of
handling your niggers. brother.

49
00:07:17.104 --> 00:07:19.857
I do with my property
as I well please.

50
00:07:19.857 --> 00:07:22.901
And you with yours.

51
00:07:22.901 --> 00:07:26.363
Daddy roll over in his grave.
he saw this.

52
00:07:26.363 --> 00:07:29.074
Let him roll.

53
00:07:29.074 --> 00:07:33.579
Say. Jockey... when is
your birthday. anyway?

54
00:07:33.579 --> 00:07:38.292
Uh. I reckon September...

55
00:07:38.292 --> 00:07:41.003
September 14.

56
00:07:41.003 --> 00:07:44.214
But it ain't but June.
Jockey.

57
00:07:44.214 --> 00:07:46.800
I reckon you right.

58
00:07:49.052 --> 00:07:51.763
How old about is you now?

59
00:07:51.763 --> 00:07:55.934
I really can't say.
Master Terrance.

60
00:07:55.934 --> 00:07:58.395
That's quite all right.
Jockey. that's...

61
00:07:58.395 --> 00:08:01.064
that's quite all right.

62
00:08:01.064 --> 00:08:04.026
I knew you let your slaves
have revels. but...

63
00:08:04.026 --> 00:08:06.445
I had no idea
they were so extravagant.

64
00:08:06.445 --> 00:08:08.238
You trying to make me look bad?

65
00:08:08.238 --> 00:08:10.240
Do not pretend you care what a
nigger thinks of you. Terrance.

66
00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:12.075
Well. you got me there.

67
00:08:12.075 --> 00:08:14.870
Let's get this parlor trick
over with. dear brother.

68
00:08:14.870 --> 00:08:17.539
I don't care to endure
this stench much longer.

69
00:08:17.539 --> 00:08:20.083
Prideful!

70
00:08:20.083 --> 00:08:22.211
Yes sir.
Master Terrance.

71
00:08:22.211 --> 00:08:26.089
Prideful. my brother

72
00:08:26.089 --> 00:08:28.717
tells me about a nigger
he has down here

73
00:08:28.717 --> 00:08:32.804
this side of the property.
S... says the boy can recite

74
00:08:32.804 --> 00:08:35.807
the Declaration of Independence.

75
00:08:35.807 --> 00:08:38.352
Now. I can't bring
myself to believe him.

76
00:08:38.352 --> 00:08:41.230
I thought. perhaps tonight
he could show me.

77
00:08:41.230 --> 00:08:43.273
since everyone is out and about

78
00:08:43.273 --> 00:08:46.902
and engaging in revelry.

79
00:08:46.902 --> 00:08:50.572
Prideful... run.
go bring me the boy

80
00:08:50.572 --> 00:08:52.741
who can recite
the Declaration. hmm?

81
00:08:55.827 --> 00:08:57.663
Michael?

82
00:08:57.663 --> 00:09:00.958
The boy with the scar
right about here. huh?

83
00:09:00.958 --> 00:09:04.586
Sorry. sir. but the boy
Michael dead and gone.

84
00:09:04.586 --> 00:09:06.296
Sickness took him.

85
00:09:08.423 --> 00:09:10.342
When?

86
00:09:10.342 --> 00:09:14.137
Maybe six...
six. seven months ago now. sir.

87
00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:17.224
I should have been told.

88
00:09:17.224 --> 00:09:20.894
Brother. you need to keep better
account of your property.

89
00:09:20.894 --> 00:09:23.605
Don't meddle.

90
00:09:23.605 --> 00:09:25.607
This boy can do it.

91
00:09:25.607 --> 00:09:27.734
No. Prideful...

92
00:09:27.734 --> 00:09:30.737
He and Michael be together
all the time.

93
00:09:30.737 --> 00:09:33.198
Let him do it.

94
00:09:35.534 --> 00:09:38.453
Well. come on. boy.
let's hear it.

95
00:09:38.453 --> 00:09:40.956
Do as master say.

96
00:09:40.956 --> 00:09:43.959
You gonna get us
all killed.

97
00:09:49.423 --> 00:09:52.759
Wh-wh-when...

98
00:09:56.555 --> 00:10:01.018
W-When in... in the course of...

99
00:10:01.018 --> 00:10:05.647
of main events... it begone...

100
00:10:05.647 --> 00:10:10.360
Well. Lord. I done
seen and heard it all now.

101
00:10:12.946 --> 00:10:16.283
When in the course
of human events

102
00:10:16.283 --> 00:10:20.162
it becomes necessary
for one people to dissolve

103
00:10:20.162 --> 00:10:23.623
the political bands which
connect them with another.

104
00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:26.251
and to assume amongst
the powers of the earth

105
00:10:26.251 --> 00:10:29.421
the separate and equal station
that the laws of nature

106
00:10:29.421 --> 00:10:33.675
and nature's God entitle them...

107
00:10:33.675 --> 00:10:38.138
I's sorry. Master. I's sorry!
Please forgive me.

108
00:10:57.282 --> 00:10:59.076
No!

109
00:13:16.004 --> 00:13:18.006
Easy.

110
00:13:19.216 --> 00:13:20.383
Drink some of this.

111
00:13:20.383 --> 00:13:22.260
Easy now. child. Easy.

112
00:13:22.260 --> 00:13:24.387
She ain't right.
you know?

113
00:13:26.681 --> 00:13:28.558
When Mabel run off and left.

114
00:13:28.558 --> 00:13:30.602
I feel like
something broke in her heart.

115
00:13:30.602 --> 00:13:32.020
Ain't been right since.

116
00:13:33.271 --> 00:13:36.149
She can still
hear youse. you know.

117
00:13:36.149 --> 00:13:40.320
How y'all talk so bad
about a girl right in her face?

118
00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:44.115
If Mabel was here.
she'd knock all hell out y'all.

119
00:13:49.621 --> 00:13:52.249
Ain't supposed
to be in here. now.

120
00:13:52.249 --> 00:13:55.460
Ain't she been beat
near to death already?

121
00:14:39.921 --> 00:14:42.591
The air
is better in here.

122
00:14:42.591 --> 00:14:44.676
It's good for you.

123
00:14:46.386 --> 00:14:48.680
What if Connelly come looking?

124
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:50.720
Don't you worry.
Won't nobody come in here.

125
00:15:10.744 --> 00:15:17.042
"But this. I conceived. was to
be the least of my misfortunes.

126
00:15:17.042 --> 00:15:21.212
For as human creatures are
observed to be more savage

127
00:15:21.212 --> 00:15:24.758
and cruel in proportion
to their bulk.

128
00:15:24.758 --> 00:15:27.761
what could I expect.
but to be a morsel

129
00:15:27.761 --> 00:15:32.974
in the mouth of the first
among these enormous barbarians

130
00:15:32.974 --> 00:15:36.394
that should happen to seize me?"

131
00:15:36.394 --> 00:15:38.772
Master cut out your tongue

132
00:15:38.772 --> 00:15:41.524
and pour poison down your
throat. he know you can read.

133
00:15:47.697 --> 00:15:50.367
What is it?

134
00:15:50.367 --> 00:15:53.870
It's called
Gulliver's Travels.

135
00:15:53.870 --> 00:15:56.122
It's about...

136
00:15:57.749 --> 00:16:00.335
...a man on a trip.

137
00:16:02.629 --> 00:16:05.173
He's lost
and trying to get home.

138
00:16:07.342 --> 00:16:10.720
In this part.
he talking about...

139
00:16:10.720 --> 00:16:14.432
giants like Goliath.

140
00:16:14.432 --> 00:16:18.645
And how. on account of them
being bigger and more powerful.

141
00:16:18.645 --> 00:16:22.607
they must also be more evil
and more cruel.

142
00:16:25.485 --> 00:16:27.862
Like white mens.

143
00:16:33.743 --> 00:16:36.246
Cora. will you come with me?

144
00:16:38.748 --> 00:16:42.711
It is past time to go.

145
00:16:44.546 --> 00:16:48.007
There is nothing here
but suffering.

146
00:16:48.007 --> 00:16:51.720
Pain and suffering.

147
00:16:52.887 --> 00:16:55.432
You're wrong about me. Caesar.

148
00:16:58.768 --> 00:17:00.895
You think I'm some kind of luck

149
00:17:00.895 --> 00:17:04.274
because my mama got away.
but you wrong.

150
00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:08.486
You wrong.

151
00:17:08.486 --> 00:17:10.697
I ain't no kind of luck.

152
00:17:10.697 --> 00:17:13.700
Only kind I had was rotten.

153
00:17:14.826 --> 00:17:17.495
The kind that cause a woman
to run away

154
00:17:17.495 --> 00:17:19.414
in the middle of the night.

155
00:17:19.414 --> 00:17:21.666
and leave her only child.

156
00:17:24.294 --> 00:17:27.839
Leave her to bleed and rot
on this damn plantation.

157
00:17:30.008 --> 00:17:32.635
That the kind of luck
you looking for?

158
00:17:39.726 --> 00:17:42.520
I'm not supposed to be here.

159
00:17:46.274 --> 00:17:48.318
But I am.

160
00:18:09.506 --> 00:18:11.424
Something wrong
with you.

161
00:18:13.885 --> 00:18:16.888
Nothing's wrong with me.

162
00:18:16.888 --> 00:18:21.351
Master says we lie
down. that means we lie down.

163
00:18:21.351 --> 00:18:24.103
Ain't no other way about it.

164
00:18:24.103 --> 00:18:26.940
Listen here.

165
00:18:26.940 --> 00:18:30.360
I know about men like you.

166
00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:32.445
You want to sneak off
in the night

167
00:18:32.445 --> 00:18:35.323
and roll around the swamp
with other mens on your back.

168
00:18:35.323 --> 00:18:37.283
that's your business.

169
00:18:37.283 --> 00:18:40.078
But here? Between us?

170
00:18:40.078 --> 00:18:42.163
Master put a man
and woman together

171
00:18:42.163 --> 00:18:44.040
because he aims to produce.

172
00:18:44.040 --> 00:18:46.042
And if that man
and that woman don't produce.

173
00:18:46.042 --> 00:18:48.253
it's for sure
gonna be a reckoning.

174
00:18:48.253 --> 00:18:50.922
you understand me?

175
00:18:50.922 --> 00:18:54.008
I won't be bred like cattle.

176
00:19:01.516 --> 00:19:04.519
You got a mighty fine heart.
Caesar.

177
00:19:04.519 --> 00:19:09.649
Pure. like Jesus Christ hisself.

178
00:19:09.649 --> 00:19:11.776
But this ain't Virginia.

179
00:19:11.776 --> 00:19:13.611
And if you don't use your sex.

180
00:19:13.611 --> 00:19:15.613
Master Randall will take it.

181
00:19:15.613 --> 00:19:18.741
He take it right off
and put it somewhere

182
00:19:18.741 --> 00:19:21.244
you won't ever have
to bother with this no more.

183
00:19:24.455 --> 00:19:28.001
You ain't no better
than the rest of us.

184
00:19:28.001 --> 00:19:31.212
And I won't suffer for you.

185
00:20:10.126 --> 00:20:11.836
Grab your things.

186
00:20:13.254 --> 00:20:14.756
Why?

187
00:20:14.756 --> 00:20:18.551
Come on now. grab your things.
don't make a ruckus.

188
00:20:18.551 --> 00:20:21.012
Come on. Prideful. set that
nigger right! Let's go!

189
00:20:21.012 --> 00:20:24.140
Yes. sir. boss. Come on now.

190
00:20:24.140 --> 00:20:25.683
- Please...
- Come on. child.

191
00:20:25.683 --> 00:20:28.269
Please. I was born in this room.

192
00:20:28.269 --> 00:20:30.063
my mama born in this room.

193
00:20:30.063 --> 00:20:31.564
- Tell him...
- Goddamn it.

194
00:20:31.564 --> 00:20:33.441
- Come on!
- No. no! No. no...

195
00:20:33.441 --> 00:20:36.027
- Grab her legs.
- No. no. no. No. no. no!

196
00:20:36.027 --> 00:20:39.030
No. No. No. No...

197
00:20:39.030 --> 00:20:40.657
- No. no!
- Grab her legs.

198
00:20:40.657 --> 00:20:43.534
No! No!

199
00:20:43.534 --> 00:20:46.245
No. no. No. no!

200
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:49.374
No! No. No.

201
00:20:49.374 --> 00:20:51.876
No! No! N-No!

202
00:20:51.876 --> 00:20:53.544
- No!
- Come on. Get up.

203
00:20:53.544 --> 00:20:56.005
No! No! No!

204
00:20:56.005 --> 00:20:57.757
- No! No!
- Come on.

205
00:20:57.757 --> 00:21:00.635
- Get on.
- No! No!

206
00:21:00.635 --> 00:21:02.387
Y'all get in there.
clean that mess up.

207
00:21:02.387 --> 00:21:04.764
I don't want none of that
hoodoo black magic mess.

208
00:21:04.764 --> 00:21:06.140
Now. come on!

209
00:21:06.140 --> 00:21:08.267
You. go!

210
00:21:08.267 --> 00:21:09.811
Hurry up!

211
00:21:14.857 --> 00:21:16.859
Make it shine!

212
00:21:44.387 --> 00:21:46.681
Run along. Hezekiah.

213
00:21:46.681 --> 00:21:48.725
- Yes. sir.
- Go on back to your mammy.

214
00:21:48.725 --> 00:21:50.476
Yes. sir. boss.

215
00:22:46.282 --> 00:22:49.077
Hold. now.

216
00:22:49.077 --> 00:22:50.536
Niggers. hold.

217
00:22:50.536 --> 00:22:52.538
All you niggers. hold!

218
00:23:05.176 --> 00:23:08.346
Y'all bow your heads. now.

219
00:23:09.722 --> 00:23:12.433
Bow your heads
for my brother. James.

220
00:23:12.433 --> 00:23:17.230
succumbed to illness.
gone on to be with God.

221
00:23:17.230 --> 00:23:19.941
Like my mama and daddy
before him.

222
00:23:19.941 --> 00:23:21.526
and like all great masters

223
00:23:21.526 --> 00:23:24.862
blessed to have received
God's grace.

224
00:23:26.072 --> 00:23:28.116
Amen.
Master Terrance.

225
00:23:28.116 --> 00:23:29.784
Amen.

226
00:23:31.244 --> 00:23:33.246
Now...

227
00:23:33.246 --> 00:23:35.623
previously. my brother and I

228
00:23:35.623 --> 00:23:37.834
shared ownership
of this fine land.

229
00:23:37.834 --> 00:23:39.460
like our great country.

230
00:23:39.460 --> 00:23:43.047
divided into north and south.

231
00:23:43.047 --> 00:23:45.633
Henceforth...

232
00:23:45.633 --> 00:23:49.512
there will be
no north and south parcels.

233
00:23:49.512 --> 00:23:53.474
We will be one plantation.

234
00:23:53.474 --> 00:23:56.727
And I shall have say
over all slaves who dwell here.

235
00:23:56.727 --> 00:24:00.314
If you wish. you may confer
with your brethren

236
00:24:00.314 --> 00:24:03.901
from the southern plantation.
but. uh...

237
00:24:03.901 --> 00:24:05.987
...my brother and I

238
00:24:05.987 --> 00:24:07.822
have a very different approach

239
00:24:07.822 --> 00:24:11.284
to the conditioning
and coordination of slaves.

240
00:24:12.410 --> 00:24:13.911
Accordingly.

241
00:24:13.911 --> 00:24:17.707
there will be no more parties.

242
00:24:17.707 --> 00:24:20.501
Wages earned in town
on Sundays

243
00:24:20.501 --> 00:24:22.211
will be subject to a tariff.

244
00:24:22.211 --> 00:24:25.673
And. to ensure the propagation
of the best stock.

245
00:24:25.673 --> 00:24:29.343
I will personally oversee
the pairing and practices

246
00:24:29.343 --> 00:24:32.597
in the ways of breeding.

247
00:24:32.597 --> 00:24:35.057
For too long. the best stock
has been reserved

248
00:24:35.057 --> 00:24:37.226
for recreational and...

249
00:24:37.226 --> 00:24:40.980
...not vocational use.

250
00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:43.316
Some of you bucks

251
00:24:43.316 --> 00:24:45.902
ain't been living
up to your billing!

252
00:25:37.036 --> 00:25:40.373
E-Everything
all right. Master Terrance?

253
00:25:41.624 --> 00:25:43.918
Everything is just fine.
Prideful.

254
00:25:47.588 --> 00:25:49.590
Everything is just fine.

255
00:26:07.316 --> 00:26:09.318
Come on!

256
00:26:11.570 --> 00:26:13.114
Come on. now!

257
00:26:15.491 --> 00:26:16.867
Come on!

258
00:26:20.413 --> 00:26:22.415
Come on. now!

259
00:26:34.093 --> 00:26:36.095
Come on!

260
00:26:50.401 --> 00:26:53.529
Come on. now!
Get in there!

261
00:27:10.254 --> 00:27:12.757
Hallelujah.

262
00:27:12.757 --> 00:27:16.385
The Lord hath smiled
on the house of Randall.

263
00:27:16.385 --> 00:27:20.306
Water the horses
before we get to the books. sir?

264
00:27:20.306 --> 00:27:21.640
That'll be fine.
Homer.

265
00:27:25.811 --> 00:27:27.813
Mm-mm-mm.

266
00:27:36.364 --> 00:27:38.449
Shall we?

267
00:27:38.449 --> 00:27:40.117
Oh. boy.

268
00:27:40.117 --> 00:27:42.119
We shall.

269
00:27:44.205 --> 00:27:45.998
Please inform Mr. Connelly

270
00:27:45.998 --> 00:27:48.459
that the prodigal
son hath returned.

271
00:28:00.304 --> 00:28:02.223
Best you ran on.

272
00:28:02.223 --> 00:28:05.684
Do you have ears
amongst your niggers here?

273
00:28:05.684 --> 00:28:09.188
Can't say
that we do.

274
00:28:09.188 --> 00:28:11.190
There are niggers
in the house. of course.

275
00:28:11.190 --> 00:28:14.318
eager to gain favor
by airing grievances

276
00:28:14.318 --> 00:28:15.986
against those
in the fields. but...

277
00:28:15.986 --> 00:28:19.115
Well. you would do well
to place some there.

278
00:28:20.157 --> 00:28:22.159
There's talk.

279
00:28:23.536 --> 00:28:27.415
There's word
of an underground railroad here.

280
00:28:27.415 --> 00:28:28.666
I-Impossible.

281
00:28:28.666 --> 00:28:30.709
Indeed.

282
00:28:31.836 --> 00:28:34.797
And yet. where do they go?

283
00:28:34.797 --> 00:28:36.966
The ones that run away and...

284
00:28:36.966 --> 00:28:39.218
never return?

285
00:28:39.218 --> 00:28:42.179
It is as though a nigger escapes

286
00:28:42.179 --> 00:28:44.348
and slips through
to a different world.

287
00:28:46.225 --> 00:28:48.227
Have you seen it?

288
00:28:48.227 --> 00:28:52.148
A man working as-as you do.
do you believe

289
00:28:52.148 --> 00:28:55.359
the underground railroad
is true?

290
00:28:55.359 --> 00:28:57.862
I have not seen it.

291
00:28:59.155 --> 00:29:03.200
But... the nigger is
a mighty cunning breed.

292
00:29:04.577 --> 00:29:08.205
Nothing about the world tells me
it is impossible.

293
00:29:08.205 --> 00:29:10.583
When I see it. I'll believe it.

294
00:29:13.169 --> 00:29:15.921
Now. to the matter at hand.

295
00:29:17.006 --> 00:29:19.425
I will not accept payment

296
00:29:19.425 --> 00:29:22.261
for the property's return.

297
00:29:22.261 --> 00:29:24.889
Consider it a recompense.

298
00:29:26.515 --> 00:29:29.852
For fulfillment of my debt
to your house.

299
00:29:30.853 --> 00:29:33.439
Good day.

300
00:29:33.439 --> 00:29:35.774
I'm sorry. I...

301
00:29:35.774 --> 00:29:37.193
I don't follow.

302
00:29:37.193 --> 00:29:39.528
Property that took
leave of here.

303
00:29:39.528 --> 00:29:42.156
many years ago
before your father passed.

304
00:29:42.156 --> 00:29:45.117
The only property
to have absconded

305
00:29:45.117 --> 00:29:47.119
and not been returned.

306
00:29:47.119 --> 00:29:51.373
I consider it
my sincerest failure.

307
00:29:51.373 --> 00:29:53.667
I know the nigger
you speak of.

308
00:29:53.667 --> 00:29:55.878
The worst kind...

309
00:29:55.878 --> 00:29:58.506
it must be said...
heartless. even for a nigger.

310
00:29:58.506 --> 00:30:00.216
Is that so?

311
00:30:00.216 --> 00:30:02.843
It is very much so.
The nigger you speak of.

312
00:30:02.843 --> 00:30:06.222
in leaving. appears to have
left behind her seed.

313
00:30:06.222 --> 00:30:08.933
A nigger girl whom. even
amongst the niggers themselves.

314
00:30:08.933 --> 00:30:11.393
is considered a monster.

315
00:30:14.104 --> 00:30:16.815
I would like an audience
with this girl.

316
00:30:20.653 --> 00:30:22.613
And a...

317
00:30:22.613 --> 00:30:24.823
an audience you shall have.

318
00:31:13.622 --> 00:31:15.624
You feel betrayed.

319
00:31:17.793 --> 00:31:19.795
As you should.

320
00:31:41.483 --> 00:31:44.445
Oh. there's anger in you.

321
00:31:47.489 --> 00:31:50.326
Best find a way
to do away with that.

322
00:31:50.326 --> 00:31:52.828
It'll eat you alive
if you don't.

323
00:31:55.205 --> 00:31:59.084
See. the heart has a way
of working through the body.

324
00:31:59.084 --> 00:32:02.671
It'll fuel you. yes. but...

325
00:32:02.671 --> 00:32:06.550
well.
it's the worst kind of fuel.

326
00:32:09.261 --> 00:32:11.263
The worst kind.

327
00:32:12.765 --> 00:32:16.352
Oh. she is within you.

328
00:32:16.352 --> 00:32:18.354
I can feel it.

329
00:32:21.857 --> 00:32:24.151
And you will run yourself
into the ground

330
00:32:24.151 --> 00:32:25.611
just to be rid of her.

331
00:32:26.904 --> 00:32:28.906
Yes. you will.

332
00:32:31.950 --> 00:32:34.578
Yes. you will.

333
00:32:38.916 --> 00:32:40.918
By God. you will.

334
00:32:55.974 --> 00:32:57.893
Sorry for the intrusion.

335
00:34:55.511 --> 00:34:59.473
"I had often read of some

336
00:34:59.473 --> 00:35:03.268
great services done
to princes and states."

337
00:35:08.398 --> 00:35:10.526
"And desired to see the persons

338
00:35:10.526 --> 00:35:15.364
by whom those services
were performed.

339
00:35:19.701 --> 00:35:24.206
Upon inquiry. I was told
that their names were...

340
00:35:24.206 --> 00:35:27.167
to be found on no record.

341
00:35:29.044 --> 00:35:31.755
Except a few of them.

342
00:35:31.755 --> 00:35:34.508
whom...
history hath represented

343
00:35:34.508 --> 00:35:37.302
as the vilest rogues
and traitors.

344
00:35:41.181 --> 00:35:45.394
As to the rest.

345
00:35:45.394 --> 00:35:49.481
I had never once heard of them.

346
00:35:49.481 --> 00:35:52.693
They all appeared
with dejected looks.

347
00:35:52.693 --> 00:35:55.279
and in the meanest habit.

348
00:35:57.322 --> 00:36:01.451
Most of them telling me
they died

349
00:36:01.451 --> 00:36:05.289
in poverty and disgrace.

350
00:36:05.289 --> 00:36:08.876
and the rest on a scaffold
or a gibbet."

351
00:36:32.900 --> 00:36:36.153
You've hardly touched your food.
Mr. Churchill.

352
00:36:36.153 --> 00:36:39.072
Oh.
Oh. pardon me. but...

353
00:36:39.072 --> 00:36:40.616
I don't understand
how one can eat

354
00:36:40.616 --> 00:36:43.702
while such a display
is taking place.

355
00:36:43.702 --> 00:36:47.831
Rather peculiar. wouldn't you
say. to eat a-and to drink

356
00:36:47.831 --> 00:36:52.044
while a man's flesh is
being ripped from his body.

357
00:36:52.044 --> 00:36:54.504
Well...

358
00:36:54.504 --> 00:36:58.050
Mr. Churchill.
your first mistake.

359
00:36:58.050 --> 00:37:01.178
uh. a nigger and a man...

360
00:37:01.178 --> 00:37:03.847
...are two entirely
different things.

361
00:37:03.847 --> 00:37:07.768
A man can think.

362
00:37:07.768 --> 00:37:10.979
reason and love.

363
00:37:12.022 --> 00:37:15.108
Niggers simply do not have
the capacity for such things.

364
00:37:15.108 --> 00:37:18.236
As such. it is important
to provide them

365
00:37:18.236 --> 00:37:20.238
with restrictions
and-and directions

366
00:37:20.238 --> 00:37:22.324
on how to comport themselves.

367
00:37:22.324 --> 00:37:25.494
And when these restrictions and
directions are not abided by.

368
00:37:25.494 --> 00:37:28.288
it is just as important...

369
00:37:28.288 --> 00:37:30.832
to make an example of them.

370
00:37:47.140 --> 00:37:50.143
Y'all come on in. now.

371
00:37:50.143 --> 00:37:53.689
Master Randall
want everybody come in.

372
00:37:55.232 --> 00:37:57.693
Y'all niggers. come on.

373
00:37:57.693 --> 00:38:00.320
Leave them sacks where they lay.

374
00:38:02.990 --> 00:38:04.992
Come on. now.

375
00:38:09.246 --> 00:38:11.289
Leave them sacks where they lay.

376
00:38:11.289 --> 00:38:13.917
Come on.

377
00:38:13.917 --> 00:38:16.837
Y'all hands. over there.

378
00:38:16.837 --> 00:38:18.839
Y'all niggers. come on.

379
00:38:20.090 --> 00:38:21.883
Come on. Lovey.

380
00:38:21.883 --> 00:38:24.928
Ruth. let's go.

381
00:38:24.928 --> 00:38:26.471
All right.

382
00:38:26.471 --> 00:38:28.223
Keep moving.

383
00:38:41.820 --> 00:38:43.321
Y'all niggers. come on.

384
00:38:55.876 --> 00:38:58.211
Gather round. my little sheep.

385
00:38:59.212 --> 00:39:01.214
Gather round.

386
00:39:04.342 --> 00:39:06.470
Today...

387
00:39:06.470 --> 00:39:08.764
I wish you all to bear witness

388
00:39:08.764 --> 00:39:11.224
to this lesson.

389
00:39:19.900 --> 00:39:22.694
"Let all who are
under a yoke as slaves

390
00:39:22.694 --> 00:39:26.907
regard their own masters
as worthy of all honor...

391
00:39:27.949 --> 00:39:29.367
...so the name of God

392
00:39:29.367 --> 00:39:31.953
and the teachings
may not be reviled.

393
00:39:31.953 --> 00:39:36.333
Those who have
believing masters...

394
00:39:37.876 --> 00:39:39.503
...must not be disrespectful

395
00:39:39.503 --> 00:39:42.339
on the ground
that they are brothers;

396
00:39:42.339 --> 00:39:45.634
rather they must serve
all the better...

397
00:39:45.634 --> 00:39:48.804
since those who benefit
from their good service

398
00:39:48.804 --> 00:39:51.681
- No more!
- are believers and beloved.

399
00:39:54.142 --> 00:39:55.727
Teach...

400
00:39:55.727 --> 00:39:57.646
teach and urge these things."

401
00:39:57.646 --> 00:40:03.318
No more mercy!
No more slaves!

402
00:40:03.318 --> 00:40:07.489
"Regard their own
masters

403
00:40:07.489 --> 00:40:09.074
as worthy of all honor."

404
00:40:10.700 --> 00:40:12.160
This is the word of God.

405
00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:15.163
- See?
- God damn you!

406
00:40:17.624 --> 00:40:20.752
God damn you!

407
00:40:20.752 --> 00:40:23.213
- What is the penalty...
- No...

408
00:40:23.213 --> 00:40:25.423
...for disobeying
the word of God?

409
00:40:25.423 --> 00:40:26.675
No!

410
00:40:27.717 --> 00:40:29.094
No!

411
00:40:31.471 --> 00:40:33.890
Damnation...

412
00:40:35.684 --> 00:40:37.477
...and eternal fire.

413
00:41:25.025 --> 00:41:27.027
It's time.

414
00:41:34.534 --> 00:41:36.254
All you niggers
get back to work.

415
00:41:39.581 --> 00:41:41.625
Quit your lollygagging.
Back to work!

416
00:41:46.129 --> 00:41:48.590
Back to work!

417
00:41:48.590 --> 00:41:49.591
Now!

418
00:48:11.931 --> 00:48:13.725
Cora?

419
00:48:13.725 --> 00:48:15.059
Lovey.

420
00:48:15.059 --> 00:48:16.603
Lovey... shh!

421
00:48:17.604 --> 00:48:19.272
I knew you was
up to something.

422
00:48:19.272 --> 00:48:21.149
Sneaking around with him
and not talking about it.

423
00:48:21.149 --> 00:48:22.650
And then you dig up them yams.

424
00:48:22.650 --> 00:48:24.027
not even ripe yet.

425
00:48:24.027 --> 00:48:26.112
Lovey. get you back
before you ruin us.

426
00:48:26.112 --> 00:48:28.865
I'm going where y'all going.

427
00:48:29.866 --> 00:48:32.035
He ain't gonna
take three of us.

428
00:48:34.370 --> 00:48:36.122
He know I'm coming?

429
00:48:42.629 --> 00:48:46.007
Well. then two surprise
as good as one.

430
00:48:46.007 --> 00:48:47.800
We got enough food. anyway.

431
00:48:50.803 --> 00:48:52.805
Come on.

432
00:49:49.779 --> 00:49:52.198
Shh!

433
00:49:52.198 --> 00:49:54.992
- ♪ Gonna give him ♪
- Shh.

434
00:49:54.992 --> 00:49:56.994
♪ All the beauty in the world...

435
00:49:56.994 --> 00:49:58.538
Lovey...

436
00:50:08.089 --> 00:50:10.299
Uh.

437
00:50:11.342 --> 00:50:13.469
Hog trail.

438
00:50:13.469 --> 00:50:14.554
Boar.

439
00:50:16.639 --> 00:50:18.516
I'm gonna check this out
right quick.

440
00:50:19.976 --> 00:50:21.936
Maybe you make use
of that whittling knife

441
00:50:21.936 --> 00:50:23.438
and catch us some dinner.

442
00:50:40.788 --> 00:50:42.206
Come here. you son of a bitch.

443
00:50:59.932 --> 00:51:01.434
No!

444
00:51:01.434 --> 00:51:02.977
No!

445
00:51:51.859 --> 00:51:53.528
Hold up.

446
00:51:53.528 --> 00:51:55.571
Where are we?

447
00:51:58.866 --> 00:52:00.910
I don't know.

448
00:52:00.910 --> 00:52:03.663
Are we going the right way?

449
00:52:03.663 --> 00:52:05.790
I don't know.

450
00:52:05.790 --> 00:52:07.416
Did you tell Lovey
where we going?

451
00:52:13.089 --> 00:52:14.924
- Did you tell...
- No.

452
00:52:18.845 --> 00:52:20.930
We were foolish
not to think on this.

453
00:52:23.266 --> 00:52:25.768
Hounds be on us soon.

454
00:52:27.603 --> 00:52:30.356
Every white man with a shotgun

455
00:52:30.356 --> 00:52:32.108
within a hundred miles gonna...

456
00:52:37.613 --> 00:52:39.198
We must keep going.

457
00:52:39.198 --> 00:52:40.575
But what about Lovey?

458
00:52:40.575 --> 00:52:42.535
What about Lovey?

459
00:52:45.162 --> 00:52:47.415
We must keep...
we must keep going.

460
00:55:14.020 --> 00:55:15.604
That's it.

461
00:55:17.148 --> 00:55:18.774
You sure?

462
00:55:20.026 --> 00:55:22.695
See that red roof there?

463
00:55:24.447 --> 00:55:26.449
That's us.

464
00:55:29.285 --> 00:55:31.203
You mean that's you.

465
00:55:31.203 --> 00:55:33.706
Don't nobody know I'm coming.

466
00:55:35.833 --> 00:55:37.918
Well. they do now.

467
00:55:42.715 --> 00:55:44.550
You ready?

468
00:57:06.549 --> 00:57:08.551
How are you managing?

469
00:57:12.221 --> 00:57:14.348
We're fine.

470
00:57:18.644 --> 00:57:21.272
Any word from the third
in our party?

471
00:57:23.190 --> 00:57:26.485
It's the talk of the state.

472
00:57:26.485 --> 00:57:29.488
From the moment you left.
it was the girl who did you in.

473
00:57:29.488 --> 00:57:31.991
They noticed her going
before they did you.

474
00:57:31.991 --> 00:57:35.619
and set out after you
on the very first night.

475
00:57:35.619 --> 00:57:37.705
And I trust that she has

476
00:57:37.705 --> 00:57:40.875
no knowledge of me or our plans.

477
00:57:40.875 --> 00:57:43.043
She does not.
No.

478
00:57:44.336 --> 00:57:46.755
There's
one other thing.

479
00:57:48.007 --> 00:57:50.467
There was a boy on the trail...

480
00:57:52.511 --> 00:57:55.931
...with a group of hunters
who lit onto you. and. well.

481
00:57:55.931 --> 00:57:58.309
he has it pretty bad
from the knock you gave him.

482
00:57:58.309 --> 00:58:01.770
They say he's in a sleep
from which he may never wake.

483
00:58:04.481 --> 00:58:06.317
Have mercy.

484
00:58:10.321 --> 00:58:12.323
Mercy for who?

485
00:58:12.323 --> 00:58:14.116
Every white man
for a hundred miles

486
00:58:14.116 --> 00:58:16.535
wants to mount your heads
on a fence.

487
00:58:22.750 --> 00:58:25.252
When the train comin'?

488
00:58:35.346 --> 00:58:37.723
Find a corner.

489
00:58:50.861 --> 00:58:54.198
- We going down there?
- Yes. indeed.

490
00:58:54.198 --> 00:58:56.325
Mind this ladder. now.

491
00:59:05.167 --> 00:59:06.669
After you.

492
01:00:09.273 --> 01:00:11.692
Now. as the train
will be here shortly.

493
01:00:11.692 --> 01:00:14.403
I just need a word
for the manifest.

494
01:00:14.403 --> 01:00:16.613
I beg your pardon?

495
01:00:16.613 --> 01:00:19.033
All who journey on the railroad

496
01:00:19.033 --> 01:00:22.411
must be documented
in the manifest.

497
01:00:22.411 --> 01:00:24.413
How else will we account

498
01:00:24.413 --> 01:00:27.833
for the souls
entrusted to this campaign?

499
01:00:27.833 --> 01:00:32.713
Now. you may speak as much
or as little as you like.

500
01:00:32.713 --> 01:00:35.966
but you must speak.

501
01:00:35.966 --> 01:00:38.552
Yeah. I'll speak
for the both of us.

502
01:00:45.893 --> 01:00:47.895
Um...

503
01:00:47.895 --> 01:00:49.897
Caesar Garner.

504
01:00:49.897 --> 01:00:53.692
Um...

505
01:00:53.692 --> 01:00:55.652
Cora Randall.

506
01:00:55.652 --> 01:00:59.740
Born to Virginia.

507
01:00:59.740 --> 01:01:03.202
Upon the death of my massa.
was promised manumission.

508
01:01:05.579 --> 01:01:09.208
Upon my massa dying.
was sold on down to Georgia.

509
01:01:11.794 --> 01:01:14.254
Cora was born
on the Randall plantation.

510
01:01:14.254 --> 01:01:16.256
That's where we met.

511
01:01:17.966 --> 01:01:20.427
Who built all this?

512
01:01:20.427 --> 01:01:23.639
Who builds anything
in this country?

513
01:01:23.639 --> 01:01:25.849
How far does it go?

514
01:01:25.849 --> 01:01:28.894
Away from here.
that's all I can tell you.

515
01:02:32.207 --> 01:02:35.752
All aboard!

516
01:02:35.752 --> 01:02:37.754
Almost forgot.

517
01:02:42.092 --> 01:02:45.012
I was keeping this for you.

518
01:02:45.012 --> 01:02:48.015
You're so close to finishing.

519
01:02:48.015 --> 01:02:51.018
Be a shame not to see it
to its conclusion.

520
01:03:09.161 --> 01:03:11.580
If you want to see
what this nation's all about.

521
01:03:11.580 --> 01:03:13.332
you got to ride the rails.

522
01:03:13.332 --> 01:03:15.375
Just look outside
as you speed through.

523
01:03:15.375 --> 01:03:18.212
and you'll see
the true face of America.

524
01:03:53.872 --> 01:03:55.624
♪ One. two ♪

525
01:03:55.624 --> 01:03:57.417
- ♪ One. two. three ♪
- ♪ Yeah! ♪

526
01:03:57.417 --> 01:03:58.961
♪ Inslumnational. underground ♪

527
01:03:58.961 --> 01:04:00.712
♪ Thunder pounds
when I stomp the ground ♪

528
01:04:00.712 --> 01:04:02.381
♪ Like a million elephants
or silverback orangutans ♪

529
01:04:02.381 --> 01:04:04.007
♪ You can't stop a train.
who want some? ♪

530
01:04:04.007 --> 01:04:05.801
♪ Don't come unprepared.
I'll be there ♪

531
01:04:05.801 --> 01:04:07.427
♪ But when I leave there.
better be a household name ♪

532
01:04:07.427 --> 01:04:09.179
♪ Weatherman tellin' us
it ain't gon' rain ♪

533
01:04:09.179 --> 01:04:10.889
♪ So now we sittin'
in a drop-top. soaking wet ♪

534
01:04:10.889 --> 01:04:12.558
♪ In a silk suit.
tryin' not to sweat ♪

535
01:04:12.558 --> 01:04:14.059
♪ Hit somersaults
without the net ♪

536
01:04:14.059 --> 01:04:15.769
♪ But this'll be the year
that we won't forget ♪

537
01:04:15.769 --> 01:04:18.230
♪ One-nine-nine-nine.
Anno Domini. anything goes ♪

538
01:04:18.230 --> 01:04:20.023
♪ Be what you wanna be.
long as you know ♪

539
01:04:20.023 --> 01:04:22.484
♪ Consequences are given
for livin'. the fence is. ♪

540
01:04:25.112 --> 01:04:28.865
There's word
of an underground railroad.

541
01:04:28.865 --> 01:04:32.619
It is as though they slip
through to a different world.

542
01:04:33.620 --> 01:04:36.164
Welcome to your future.

543
01:04:36.164 --> 01:04:38.750
This is real. Cora.

544
01:04:38.750 --> 01:04:40.669
You here.
I'm here.

545
01:04:40.669 --> 01:04:41.795
We here.

546
01:04:42.921 --> 01:04:46.008
Together.
we are building

547
01:04:46.008 --> 01:04:49.261
a better mind
for the practical betterment

548
01:04:49.261 --> 01:04:50.596
of Negro mind!

549
01:04:50.596 --> 01:04:52.931
There are things
happening here

550
01:04:52.931 --> 01:04:54.891
that we don't really understand.

551
01:04:54.891 --> 01:04:56.685
There's a train coming.

552
01:04:59.688 --> 01:05:01.064
- Your name?
- Cora Randall.

553
01:05:01.064 --> 01:05:03.900
I took the Underground
from South Carolina.

554
01:05:03.900 --> 01:05:05.527
Should have stayed there.

555
01:05:06.570 --> 01:05:09.239
The girl
in that bulletin is wanted

556
01:05:09.239 --> 01:05:10.824
for the murder of a child.

557
01:05:10.824 --> 01:05:13.493
I'm gonna get us out of here.
I promise.

558
01:05:14.995 --> 01:05:16.788
Hello. little missy.

559
01:05:16.788 --> 01:05:19.666
We've been waiting on you.

560
01:05:19.666 --> 01:05:21.668
You came all this way
on the Railroad?

561
01:05:21.668 --> 01:05:23.629
And left behind
all those peoples.

562
01:05:23.629 --> 01:05:26.632
I'm still just a runaway
from Georgia.

563
01:05:26.632 --> 01:05:28.216
You're safe here. Cora.

564
01:05:28.216 --> 01:05:31.595
Ain't no way he ever
giving up on finding me.

565
01:05:31.595 --> 01:05:33.680
I need you

566
01:05:33.680 --> 01:05:36.808
to be strong. watchful.
Like me.

567
01:05:38.894 --> 01:05:41.480
This wonderful place...

568
01:05:42.773 --> 01:05:44.816
...built out of Black love

569
01:05:44.816 --> 01:05:47.277
and spirit.

570
01:05:47.277 --> 01:05:51.073
We can escape slavery.

571
01:05:52.282 --> 01:05:55.661
And yet its scars
will never fade.

572
01:06:19.017 --> 01:06:21.311
Everything that you ever knew

573
01:06:21.311 --> 01:06:23.605
told you that freedom

574
01:06:23.605 --> 01:06:25.982
was a delusion.

575
01:06:29.778 --> 01:06:32.823
And yet here we are.
